title: [ICE]: 'attempt to add with overflow', compiler/rustc_errors/src/emitter.rs:2229:17

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-debug-assertions
labels.description: This issue requires debug-assertions in some way

body:
### Code

```Rust
#![warn(explicit_outlives_requirements)]

macro_rules! tuple_impls {
    ($($name:ident)+) => {
        struct TupleInPlaceVisitor<'a, $($name: 'a,)+>(&'a ($($name,)+));
    }
}

mod ok {
    tuple_impls!(T0 T1 T2 T3 T4 T5 T6 T7 T8 T9 T10 T11);
}

mod ice {
    tuple_impls!(T0 T1 T2 T3 T4 T5 T6 T7 T8 T9 T10 T11 T12);
}
```


### Affected release channels

- [ ] Previous Stable
- [ ] Current Stable
- [ ] Current Beta
- [ ] Current Nightly

master at c0b87359599629d69a7b37318088dac3a5d67c9c with debug assertions
